The evidence with the title 'UK is violent crime capital of Europe - Telegraph ' says Nov 11, 2015  ... It means there are over 2,000 crimes recorded per 100,000 population in the UK , making it the most violent place in Europe. Austria is second, with a rate of 1,677 per 100,000 people, followed by. Sweden, Belgium, Finland and Holland. By comparison, America has an estimated rate of 466 violent crimes  ... 
